      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-290" title="kotong-cops" src="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/kotong-cops.jpg" alt="kotong-cops" width="265" height="359" /></a>It was October 8, 2010 around 7pm, This month of October is a gun banned condition for all of barangay’s(village) here in the Philippines, because of coming barangay election in October 25.<br />
While I was driving in the amidst of Mcarthur hi-way, I was pulled by one of the traffic law enforcer wearing black uniform, At that moment I have a suspicion that I will be fall behind and pay 1000 pesos for my penalty and I will have a minute of interview to the law abiding officer. But as always expected as said by the others who have experienced caught by a “parak”,”buwaya”,&#8221;<strong>kotong cops</strong>&#8221; and whatever they called this greedy law breakers. He ask for a piece of cake or what we called “lagay”, He ask me “how much money you have there?, thought just how much he said. I said is 100 pesos is enough? He said No, No.. can you increase it to 200 pesos?. I think for a second, Ok ok is 150 is enough I said, ahmmmmm he sigh and said.. Ok Ok that is enough. I just wondering now that law here in the Philippines can now be bought for just a 150 pesos, and that can be auctioned up to 50 pesos if the law abiding officer is strongly in need, LOL, because once my friend has said to me that when he was caught by this “parak” he only pays 50 pesos, if we will convert, it will just be a single dollar.<br />
But there is some mistake done by the officer, how was it?. Here it is, I told him that I do not have yet money on my pocket and I will be going to withdraw some cash on the ATM, for assurance I left my student licensed and official receipt to him and ASKED FOR HER NAME, HE ANSWERED, OK JUST GET BACK SOON AND TRY TO ASK MY NAME TO THOSE OTHER OFFICERS THERE, MY NAME IS “<strong>JUNE TECSON</strong>”, and he whisper…just tell them that I am your uncle.</p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com">Up Quotes</a> blog where you can read the greatest quotes and famous quotations.</p>


