      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Fishbal-greatest-quotes.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-181" title="Fishbal - greatest quotes" src="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Fishbal-greatest-quotes.jpg" alt="Fishbal by: greatest quotes" width="250" height="166" /></a>&#8220;Hindi Ko Pa Naranasang Magmahal Kahit Minsan &#8211; Fishball(Php 0.50 since 1992)&#8221;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In English “I do never experienced to become expensive &#8211; Fishball(Php 0.50 since 1992)” brought to you by the <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com" >greatest quotes</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">It is really unbelievable in spite of economical and financial crisis still fish ball is not increasing in price. Commonly in the Philippines fish ball is one of the best and well-known street foods that has cheap but reasonable taste. I do remember since I was a child that every time I see a fish ball cart I always see a bunch of people surrounding and having some sticks in hand and making “tusok-tusok”(sting) to the Kawali(frying pan). In the Philippines, locals not only have fish balls, but squid balls as well. These seafood balls are sold skewered on bamboo sticks and dished in a variety of sauces as street food. The fish-ball is enjoyed as a nibble and is very well-liked. Fish ball stands in this country seem to operate in much the same way a hot dog stand does in the US.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Citizens from HongKong differentiate two kinds of fish balls. One kind is eaten with noodles, while another, more yellow kind is sold in &#8220;strings&#8221; or skewers in food stalls.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">In Singapore and Malaysia, fish balls may be found in soups, noodles, and served with rice. They are sold in hawker stalls. They even have fish balls that are filled with pork also, which are called <em>fuzhou </em>fish balls.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Kaya Kung hindi mo pa naranasang Magmahal.Isipin mo lang na hindi ka nag-iisa, dahil may karamay ka…Fishball 0.50php since 1992 .Articles original posted  by the <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com" >greatest quotes</a> and company.</p>
