      <description>To be called a great is a very high level of respect and gratitude, Greatness is a perception of a state of supremacy. The notion carries the nuance that the particular person or object, Greatness shows clear and perceivable advantage among others. To be entitled a Great Man you must have the guts, power, wealth, [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com"&gt;Up Quotes&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can read the greatest quotes and famous quotations.&lt;/p&gt;



Similar best wisdom quotes:&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href='http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/greatest-quotes-on-july-14-2010' rel='bookmark' title='Permanent Link: Greatest Quotes on &amp;#8211; July 14, 2010'&gt;Greatest Quotes on &amp;#8211; July 14, 2010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/once-said-by-the-wise/Once_Said_By_The_Wise-THE_GREATEST_MAN_IN_HISTORY.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a title="arenenberg" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/84609865@N00/4043272465/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3232/4043272465_39007a5e51_m.jpg" border="0" alt="greatest man in history" width="167" height="240" /></a>To be called a great is a very high level of respect and gratitude, Greatness is a perception of a state of supremacy. The notion carries the nuance that the particular person or object, Greatness shows clear and perceivable advantage among others. To be entitled a Great Man you must have the guts, power, wealth, and influence in all aspects of life like politics, authority to the people and the supremacy among others. Some of the said greatest men in history like Alexander the Great has won so many battles and always bring the bacon of victory to its nation. Another one is Julius Caesar, who has great influence when it comes to politics; He was a Roman military and political leader, He played a decisive role in the renovation of the Roman Republic into the Roman Empire. There are so many Great Leaders that was written in the books and make great contributions in the history. There are so many aspects that a great man must have. But I was astonished when I knew that being a great is not a attainable within this aspects, like political power, authority to the people, thousands of army and an empire.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Jesus had no servants, yet they called Him Master.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He had no degree, yet they called Him Teacher.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He does not have a lot of medicines and doctorate degree, yet they called Him a healer.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He does not have thousands of army, yet kings feared Him.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He won no military battle, yet He conquered the world.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">He committed no crime, yet they crucified Him. He was buried in a tomb, Yet He lives today.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If I have a to choose among all the great leaders in the world, I will go for Jesus Christ. Feel the Honor to</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">serve such a wonderful leader who loves us much.<br />
