      <description>Wisdom is a profound perceptive and realization of different matters like people,  things, places, proceedings or situations, that results in the capability to decide time after time to produce the finest outcome with a least of instance and energy. To make it short Wisdom is the ability to optimally apply perceptions and knowledge to produce [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com"&gt;Up Quotes&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can read the greatest quotes and famous quotations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/once-said-by-the-wise/Once_Said_By_The_Wise-THE_SECRET_TO_GAIN_WISDOM_IS_U_D_R_T_N_I_G.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: justify;"><a title="We Don't" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/56667362@N00/95601149/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none;" src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/43/95601149_11a45d3217.jpg" border="0" alt="Christian wisdom" width="301" height="228" /></a><strong> </strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Wisdom</strong> is a profound perceptive and realization of different matters like people,  things, places, proceedings or situations, that results in the capability to decide time after time to produce the finest outcome with a least of instance and energy. To make it short <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >Wisdom</a> is the ability to optimally apply perceptions and knowledge to produce the desired results. Moreover <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >Wisdom</a> is the discerning of what is true and what is not.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">I’ve always remember this biblical verse whenever the word &#8220;<a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >wisdom</a>&#8221; comes into my mind, it was written in Proverbs 4:7 where it say’s “Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >wisdom</a>: and with all thy getting get U_D_R_T_N_I_G.“, When I am in my elementary years way back in 1996 up to my college days this sense was not being implemented in my mind and acts. Whenever we have a test, the day before I always kept on reviewing and do a lot of reading and memorizing. From top up to bottom of the pages of the paper I memorized it. So the day of the examination came, perfectly I’ve always get the correct answers to each of the questions, that is simply because I reviewed a lot and I have memorized the reviewer manuscript. But after a couple of days all the things that I have reviewed were always vanished in my brain, so the next time I will encounter the questions on the test paper I have to review it once again, and again, and again.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">One time while watching television I was enticed to this preacher named Bro. “E” who taught of <strong>Christian wisdom</strong> and <strong>truth quotes</strong> based on the <strong>bible scriptures</strong>. He read about the <strong>sayings phrases</strong> written in the Proverbs 4:7 and it is about <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >wisdom</a>, it say’s there that “Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >wisdom</a>: and with all thy getting get U_D_R_T_N_I_G.“. I was all of a sudden jumped in delight because of that verse, AHA! I think this is the missing why I&#8217;ve always forgotten the essence of every manuscript I reviewed in spite of so much reading and memorizing , Now I know what I am lacking, it is simply “UNDERSTANDING”.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Thanks be to God and second thanks  to that Bro.”E” who taught me accidentally about the secret to gain <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/biblical-verse/the-secret-to-gain-wisdom/" >wisdom</a>. Now it’s not a secret anymore.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" rel="nofollow" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com/wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="wheeldog" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/56667362@N00/95601149/" target="_blank">wheeldog</a></small></p>
<p>This post via the <a href="http://www.oncesaidbythewise.com">Up Quotes</a> blog where you can read the greatest quotes and famous quotations.</p>


